1
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:11,280
Had a nightmare.

2
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,640
Can you stop wearing that creepy mask?

3
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:22,040
Waving it around in my face.

4
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:23,840
It's so lame.

5
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:30,880
You know what?

6
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,440
That shady agency got reported.

7
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,800
Word is, an insider reported them.

8
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:38,200
People said when it got shut down,

9
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:40,280
all of them looked totally unhinged.

10
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,200
If you ask me,

11
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,720
that's karma right there.

12
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:44,800
No one escapes it.

13
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:47,600
Zhou Yi has a point.

14
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:48,920
Don't judge a book by its cover.

15
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,200
Looks can be deceiving.

16
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,160
A pretty exterior

17
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,760
doesn't mean a pure heart.

18
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:55,720
An ugly exterior

19
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:57,800
doesn't mean a dirty soul.

20
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,200
Uncle Wang is right.

21
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,280
Like that flipped apartment.

22
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:04,920
Looked nice,

23
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,800
but it was actually toxic.

24
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,680
And kind-hearted Granny Sun

25
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,520
was treated like a crazy person by everyone.

26
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,520
Look who's here.

27
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,680
Master Lin.

28
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,160
Thank you.

29
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,160
I can't accept this.

30
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,280
No, no, really.

31
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,640
It's just a small token from us.

32
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,200
Please take it.

33
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,560
Master Lin,

34
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,200
my husband's health

35
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,120
lately

36
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:34,080
has been so much better than before.

37
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,800
I really

38
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,120
have to thank you, Master Lin.

39
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:38,920
Thank you so much.

40
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,400
What you said that day...

41
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,920
You're too kind.

42
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,360
It's the least we could do.

43
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,840
There's more good news.

44
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,320
Xiao Bai had her baby.

45
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:47,240
Mother and baby are doing well.

46
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,000
She said thanks to us catching it in time,

47
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,760
the baby's perfectly healthy.

48
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,120
That's wonderful.

49
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,280
Mr. He,

50
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,120
come have some tea over here.

51
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:56,600
Yes, yes, please.

52
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,560
Lin You,

53
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,240
you changed way too much in this adaptation.

54
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,760
You made Granny Sun a mute!

55
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,680
Just be happy with it.

56
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,840
At least it's a happy ending.

57
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:16,800
Where are you going?

58
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,480
I'm going to Granny Sun's today.

59
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,480
I need to buy some things.

60
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,080
Uncle, Uncle Wang,

61
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,120
enjoy your tea.

62
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:27,960
Off you go.

63
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:29,840
Please, please.

64
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,080
Where should we hang this?

65
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,320
Just hang it on that wall.

66
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,760
Help!

67
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:48,760
Is anyone there?

68
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,040
Is anybody there?

69
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:57,000
Help me!

70
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:58,400
Help!

71
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,680
Sister Na!

72
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,720
No, no!

73
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,240
Sister Na!

74
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,680
Sister Na!

75
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,880
Sister Na!

76
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:20,200
Bring the takeout to my office.

77
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:23,160
No one else is at the office today.

78
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:39,360
Help!

79
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,960
Help me!

80
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:41,800
Help...

81
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,640
Somebody, help!

82
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,480
Is anyone there?

83
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,200
Sister Na!

84
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:10,640
What's wrong?

85
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,800
The elevator...

86
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,240
There's something in the elevator!

87
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,080
Something?

88
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,320
What kind of thing?

89
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,160
What's going on with the office?

90
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:41,640
Why did the power go out?

91
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,560
There's a ghost in the office.

92
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:44,480
Let's get out of here.

93
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,200
You light the way.

94
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,120
We'll follow you. Hurry up.

95
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,240
Let's just get out first.

96
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,280
Wait, no.

97
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,880
We can't take the elevator.

98
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:53,120
We have to take the stairs.

99
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:53,920
Okay.

100
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:56,640
Wait, hold on.

101
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,880
I just saw Old Zhang.

102
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,040
He hasn't left yet.

103
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,600
Let's just go.

104
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,360
It's pitch black, where are we supposed to find him?

105
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,920
Let's go downstairs and call him.

106
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,600
Did you find Old Zhang later?

107
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,520
We couldn't reach him on the phone.

108
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:34,920
Later, the power came back on.

109
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,320
And he came running out on his own.

110
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,760
He said something in the cabinet grabbed him.

111
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:39,920
He passed out from fear.

112
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,440
Then he struggled free and ran out.

113
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,520
Later, when Mr. Qin found out,

114
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,240
he told Old Zhang to figure something out,

115
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:49,000
and sublet the place as soon as possible.

116
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,720
And Old Zhang pushed it onto me.

117
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:57,560
I figured

118
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,680
you handle this sort of thing,

119
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,960
and deal with property rentals,

120
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,400
so I came to you.

121
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:08,480
Mr. Lu.

122
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:10,280
Blessings of the Heavenly Lord.

123
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,160
Please, rest assured.

124
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,760
Great Luck Agency

125
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,800
will definitely get to the bottom

126
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,760
of your company's situation.

127
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:20,160
And sublet your space as soon as possible.

128
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:21,760
However,

129
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,080
right now, the situation

130
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,320
isn't quite clear yet.

131
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,800
We don't know if it's someone's doing,

132
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:27,760
or...

133
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:28,600
that kind of thing.

134
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:29,960
Here's what we'll do.

135
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,200
Liu Liu.

136
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,120
Lin You.

137
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,920
You two go back with Mr. Lu.

138
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:35,440
As for you,

139
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,240
handle the on-site investigation.

140
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,560
Take some photos and bring them back.

141
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:39,680
Liu Liu,

142
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,600
you go talk to the three people involved.

143
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:44,800
Uncle Wang.

144
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,640
What about you?

145
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:48,920
It's getting late.

146
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,880
I'll go make some dinner.

147
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,040
Old Wang, seriously...

148
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,560
He's just dumping the work on us.

149
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,080
If he had come with us,

150
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:14,960
maybe,

151
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,120
on this trip today,

152
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,520
we would've wrapped everything up.

153
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:26,640
What are you looking at?

154
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,400
I was just thinking,

155
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,600
you were right earlier.

156
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,400
Right.

157
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:55,800
Um...

158
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,160
Why don't we take the stairs?

159
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:01,920
Why?

160
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,240
Didn't Lu Can say

161
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,880
this elevator is really creepy?

162
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,400
Sure.

163
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,880
Taking the stairs is good exercise.

164
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,800
Let's go.

165
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,280
Lin You.

166
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,160
Lin You.

167
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:03,560
Lin You.

168
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,600
How about we take the elevator instead?

169
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:17,720
Help me, help me, help me!

170
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:19,920
Help me, help me, help me!

171
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:21,280
Just...

172
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,160
It was just like that.

173
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,480
You two didn't see it.

174
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:27,400
It yanked me so hard, it really hurt!

175
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,000
It must have been that thing.

176
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,880
Its fingernails were super long.

177
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:31,480
Look.

178
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:32,480
Look.

179
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,440
It scratched me up.

180
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:34,000
See?

181
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,400
Mr., Mr. Zhang.

182
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,400
About the situation in your office,

183
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,200
we have a pretty good understanding of it now.

184
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,080
Um...

185
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,200
Could we also

186
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,680
speak with the other two colleagues

187
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,440
to get more details?

188
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:47,840
No problem.

189
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,040
I'll go get them.

190
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:50,360
Okay, great, great.

191
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,240
Thank you, thank you.

192
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:56,360
Lin You.

193
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,120
You go take photos,

194
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,480
and I'll take notes.

195
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,080
You...

196
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:12,200
can you handle it?

197
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,920
Can you handle it on your own?

198
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:24,680
Who are you looking down on?

199
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,400
It's still early.

200
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,400
I'll sleep a bit more.

201
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,480
That night, only the four of us were at the office.

202
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,600
When I went downstairs that day,

203
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,280
the three of them were all working.

204
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,560
There was no one else in the elevator.

205
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:11,200
Then, after that rope fell,

206
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,720
how did you get out?

207
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:15,640
The elevator just returned to normal later.

208
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:16,800
When it reached this floor,

209
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,360
the doors just opened on their own.

210
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,320
It was terrifying.

211
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,400
And then I ran into you.

212
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:28,560
Right.

213
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,360
When I was about to help Sister Na up,

214
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,000
all the lights suddenly went out.

215
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,520
And then...

216
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,560
we saw it.

217
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,240
That thing.

218
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:43,280
What thing?

219
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:52,560
This thing.

220
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:55,040
Have you seen it before?

221
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,040
No.

222
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,560
Couldn't really tell.

223
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:06,240
Just that typical long hair,

224
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:09,120
with pitch-black hollow eyes,

225
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,360
and its mouth wide open.

226
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,240
Wang Yu, you tell him.

227
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,160
Don't you have good eyesight?

228
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:18,320
I didn't get a clear look.

229
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,360
The noose...

230
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:28,840
appeared right here.

231
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:30,360
Master Lin.

232
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,080
The top of the elevator.

233
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:34,080
We had someone open it and check this morning.

234
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:35,120
There was nothing.

235
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,720
But something could definitely get in through here.

236
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,640
You just push this cover like this,

237
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:40,880
and it opens.

238
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:46,560
Master Lin.

239
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,040
Master Lin.

240
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,400
Master Lin.

241
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,520
Why don't we go check the workstations?

242
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:56,120
Okay.

243
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:58,680
Let's take the stairs.

244
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,720
So after you got out and met Xiao Na,

245
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:13,800
what happened next?

246
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,640
We ran into Lu Can.

247
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,920
Lu Can was terrified too.

248
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:26,720
After the three of us ran out of the building,

249
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,920
all the lights in the office suddenly came back on.

250
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,360
So you're saying,

251
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,720
Lu Can might have seen that thing too?

252
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,320
He said

253
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,600
he also saw a figure dart by.

254
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,440
And later that day,

255
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,520
he was the only one who

256
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:45,000
went back inside to grab his laptop.

257
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:51,160
Is his laptop that important?

258
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,520
How could he dare go back for it?

259
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,960
That thing probably wouldn't hurt him anyway.

260
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,840
He's just an intern who recently joined.

261
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,440
He's not close with anyone here.

262
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:07,800
So...

263
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,320
this "she"

264
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:12,560
is someone you all know well?

265
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:26,040
Master Lin.

266
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,560
There's nothing in this stairwell.

267
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:30,000
Why don't we go back and take the elevator?

268
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:45,880
Why?

269
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:47,720
I've already tried so hard.

270
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,480
Why are you doing this to me?

271
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:50,840
Why, Lu Can?

272
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,520
Calm down, calm down.

273
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:53,800
Just calm down.

274
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,160
You need to calm down.

275
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:02,400
Let's go take a look too.

276
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,120
I'm not going, I'm not going. Let's go.

277
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:05,960
Lu Can.

278
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:07,200
Why are you helping him?

279
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:07,760
Stop it.

280
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,280
Let go!

281
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:12,120
Why, Lu Can?

282
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:13,680
Why, Lu Can?

283
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:14,800
Why, Lu Can?

284
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:15,680
Lu Can!

285
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:20,560
Answer me!

286
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:21,880
Say something!

287
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:47,320
Kid,

288
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,360
the ghost attached to you

289
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,680
is quite a beauty.

290
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:02,760
This guy Lu Can

291
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,880
has a lot of women's items at his desk.

292
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,000
Going through a woman's things casually

293
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,280
isn't very polite, is it?

294
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,319
